title: Publishers will see no meaningful AI licensing revenue
description: Publishers have been waiting for another round of licensing deals with artificial intelligence companies. The first few agreements were small but encouraging. They suggested the industry might finally get paid for the journalism that underpins so much of the output of AI large language models. That optimism won’t survive 2026. As long as Google’s search...
